 GitHub Repositories Portfolio

This web application is designed to showcase GitHub repositories in a user-friendly portfolio format. It utilizes the GitHub API to fetch and display repository data, including details like the repository name, description, and programming language used. The app features pagination, search, and filter capabilities, as well as detailed views for individual repositories.

 Features

- List all GitHub repositories with pagination.
- Search and filter functionality for the repositories list.
- Detailed view for individual repository information.
- Error handling with a custom error boundary.
- Responsive and accessible UI design.

 Installation

To get started with this project, clone the repository and install the dependencies:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YourUsername/github-repo-portfolio.git
cd github-repo-portfolio
npm install
```

Usage

To run the application locally:

```bash
npm start
```

Navigate to `http://localhost:3000` in your web browser to view the application.

